snippet.textDisplay:
I am in southern China and in my city [Nanning] most people have been wearing masks but some are not, maybe because the chemists have sold out very quickly. It is very quiet in the neighbourhood and feels a bit like a science fiction movie. My fridge is almost empty and the online supermarkets have dramatically increased their prices, eg: a litre of orange juice has increased from 9 RMB [about 90p] to 50 RMB [5 Pounds] and other food products have increased as well. However to be fair the government are really doing a great job to contain the virus by extending the public holiday and lockingdown some cities. We have been told to wait until 8th February before the peak of the virus has passed. The start of the school term has also be postponed until further notice.
Show less
REPLY
